-- Bosch Forecasts Sales in Turkey to Rise 19% This Year, Haberturk Reports
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2010-09-27T06:08:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/bosch-forecasts-sales-in-turkey-to-rise-19-this-year-haberturk-reports.html
Robert Bosch GmbH , a German vehicle
components maker, expects to increase its sales in Turkey 19
percent to 750 million euros this year, Haberturk reporter,
citing chairman  Franz Fehrenbach .  The company, which operates in Turkey through its unit
 Bosch Fren Sistemleri AS , announced plans on Sept. 24 to invest
500 million euros ($673.6 million) in Turkey until the end of
2013, Fehrenbach said in a news conference in Istanbul,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ercan Ersoy  in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 